WAKAWAKA / "Compro o quê?!" — third-party attribution
======================================================

Screen B charting (public/index.html) loads two third-party libraries from a CDN at
runtime (buildless; they are NOT vendored/redistributed in this repository):

1) TradingView Lightweight Charts™
   - Source: https://github.com/tradingview/lightweight-charts (v5)
   - License: Apache License 2.0
   - © TradingView, Inc. Used under the terms of the Apache-2.0 license, which requires
     attribution to TradingView. The on-chart attribution logo is intentionally disabled
     in this private/internal tool; this NOTICE preserves the required attribution.

2) lightweight-charts-drawing (drawing tools — Fase VII)
   - Package: lightweight-charts-drawing@0.1.1 (deepentropy)
   - License: MIT
   - Loaded via CDN (unpkg) as a UMD bundle; `lightweight-charts` is its peer dependency,
     so it operates on this app's existing v5 chart instance (no second copy).
   - Note: at v0.1.1 the library renders/edits/persists drawings and handles selection +
     anchor-dragging, but it does not implement interactive *creation* from the active tool;
     the click-to-place-anchors creation flow is implemented in public/index.html on top of
     the library's tool registry (createDrawing) + DrawingManager (addDrawing/export/import).
